<|startoftext|>Dish: chicken nut bars
Directions: pre heat oven to 350 degrees
in a mixing bowl , combine the flour , rolled oats , and butter
make a well in the center , set the buttermilk aside for later
beat together the egg , milk , sugar , and salt until well blended
stir in the buttermilk mixture
fold in the pecans
line a 13x9 loaf pan with the dough
pour the buttermilk mixture evenly over the bread
bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes , or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean
remove the bread from the oven and let cool on a wire rack
store in the refrigerator
filling:
mix dry ingredients in a large bowl using a dough hook or the flatest portion of a wooden spoon
in another bowl combine the egg substitute , beaten egg yolk , and vanilla
add the dry ingredients and mix only until the dry ingredients are moistened
shape the dough into a patty-like shape on a greased cookie sheet
flatten with the heel of your hand
bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes or until lightly browned on the bottom , and the crust is firm
store in a jar to keep warm
in a medium saucepan melt the butter and drizzle half the hot syrup over the baked bread
drizzle the remaining syrup over the bread , allowing some to run over the side'<|endoftext|>
